Package edu.missouristate.taschedulegenerator.algorithm

Class TAScheduler

java.lang.Object
edu.missouristate.taschedulegenerator.algorithm.TAScheduler
All Implemented Interfaces:
Runnable
public class TAScheduler
extends Object
implements Runnable
Allows for creating multiple genetic algorithms, timing them, and collecting the best results from each.
Author:
Noah Geren

      public static Future<?> schedule​(List<TA> tas, List<Course> courses, Consumer<List<Schedule>> callback, Consumer<Exception> errorCallback)
      Starts scheduling TAs and courses.
      Parameters:

      callback - The callback function for when generating schedules completes.
      errorCallback - The callback function used when an uncaught expection is thrown.
      Returns:
      A Future object that can be used to cancel generating schedules.

    • run

      public void run()
      Starts the timer and genetic algorithm threads. Order of execution:
      1. Start genetic algorithm threads
      2. Sleep for SLEEP_TIME_MILLISECONDS until reaching MAX_RUNTIME_MILLISECONDS
      3. Interrupt genetic algorithm threads
      4. Collect best results from each genetic algorithm
      5. Sort and return the MAX_SCHEDULES best schedules
      Specified by:
      run in interface Runnable
      See Also:
      MAX_THREADS, MAX_RUNTIME_MILLISECONDS, SLEEP_TIME_MILLISECONDS, MAX_SCHEDULES
